<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1897-05-12T00:28:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1897-05-12T00:28:00-05:00" n="469" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d469">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Barrett</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Sherman</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Bangkok</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1897-05-12T12:10:00+06:42"><hi rend="italic">May 12,
                                        1897—12.10 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>Hannen telegraphs will act arbitrator if British minister for foreign
                            affairs approves. I would advise you to communicate with the British
                            minister for foreign affairs as soon as possible. Siamese Government
                            doing it.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Barrett.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>